<p>
playing a card from hand
1. check requirements
    must meet requirements
    must be able to perfrom the effect
        e.g. if a card effect has negative energy production, you must be able to decrease energy production to play it
        exceptions:
            play a card that raises a maxed-out parameter, or
            adds resources you cannot collect (e.g. add microbes to another card, but no other cards collect microbes), or
            removes resources from another player (when you cannot or do not want to)

2. pay & gain immediate effects
    pay card cost
    lower panel shows any immediate effects
    the card's effects, and any effects that the card triggers, are performed in any order of the player's choice
    brown box production is mandatory
    red frame resource or production affects any 1 player of your choice (including self)
    tiles & tags with a red border means it targets any player's tiles or tags
    non-standard resources (animals, microbes, etc) are collected on specific cards - by default on the card that generates them
    asterisk (*) denotes exception to normal rules; read card
3. place card appropriately
    red Event cards are collected facedown, tags only apply while being played
    green Automated cards have no further effects, but tags still apply
    blue Active cards have ongoing effects
</p>

