<h3>Turmoil</h3>

<h4>Summary</h4>
<ul>
    <li>6 parties; 1 is the <b>Dominant Party</b> and 1 is the <b>Ruling Party</b>
        <ul>
            <li>can be the same party</li>
            <li>dominant party: most delegates</li>
            <li>party leader of the dominant party becomes the chairman during Turmoil step of Solar phase (gain 1 TR)</li>
            <li>ruling party: dominant party from last round; ruling bonus triggers (once) and a new policy changes a game rule</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Global event cards show what will happen in coming generations
        <ul>
            <li>initial flip (distant event): add delegate using top-left symbol</li>
            <li>slide to center (coming event): no additional delegate</li>
            <li>final card slide (current event): add delegate using mid-right symbol</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Global Events
        <ul>
            <li>Count the given parameter, but limit of 5</li>
            <li>Influence can then adjust the count (possibly beyond 5)</li>
            <li>Each player can have 0-3 influence, 1 point of influence for
                <ol>
                    <li>Chairman</li>
                    <li>Party leader of <b>dominant party</b></li>
                    <li>At least 1 non-leader delegate of <b>dominant party</b></li>
                </ol>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>



<h4>Lobbying</h4>
(new action, NOT a standard project)
move one of your delegates into the delegate area of your desired party on the Terraforming Committee board
    $5 from delegate reserve
    $0 from the Lobby

Delegates
---
1+ delegates in the delegate area of the dominant party gives 1 influence
a delegate can also be party leader or chairman, giving 1 influence each

party leader
---
    first delegate placed in a party automatically becomes party leader
    any player (including neutral) who has more delegates in a party than the current party leader -> replace party leader with their own
        old party leader becomes normal delegate for the party
    also counts as a delegate for the party
    party leader in the dominant party counts as 1 influence; will become chairman in turmoil phase
chairman
---
    when dominant party becomes ruling party, the party leader becomes chairman
    delegate moves to chairman seat and that player gets 1 TR

dominant party
---
party with the most delegates
dominant party becomes ruling party next generation
party becomes ruling -> delegates returned to their reserves, dominance marker is shifted to the new party with the most delegates
    more than 1 party tied for most: dominance marker is moved clockwise from the new ruling party, going to first in line

ruling party
---
active policy tile shows which party is ruling
effect/action on the policy tile is only active during the Action phase
party becomes ruling -> appoints a new chairman and applies a ruling bonus

becoming ruling
---
Solar phase -> Turmoil -> step 3
dominant party becomes ruling party, replacing old ruling party
place party's policy tile on top of the pile
ruling bonus of new party is applied to all players
old chairman and all delegates in the ruling party return to reserves
party leader becomes new chairman
that player gains 1 TR
dominance marker shifts
lobby is refilled

Lobby
---
start of each generation: each player gets 1 delegate in the lobby
may place the delegate in a party as a free lobbying action
end of each generation: each spent delegate in the loby is replaced by a new delegate from the delegate reserve

neutral delegates
---
count as a separate player
can become party leader and chairman

project card requirements
---
may show icon of a party -> only playable if that party is currently the ruling party OR if you have 2+ delegates in that party

influence
---
any global event that counts resources, production, cards, tiles, tags, etc. can count a maximum of 5
the count (max 5) can then be modified up/down (including beyond 5) by influence
a player has 0-3 influence, based on
    owning chairman = 1 inf
    owning leader of dominant party = 1 inf
    owning 1+ non-leader delegates of dominant party = 1 inf

TR Revision
---
at start of Turmoil phase, after production, all players lose 1 TR

Distant Global Event
---
Global Event reveal: add a neutral delegate in the party indicated by the card

Coming Global Event
---
when card transitions from COMING -> CURRENT, place a neutral delegate in the party indicated by the card

Current Global Event
---
Turmoil phase, end of the generation
current event effect is performed
if "first player" makes a decision they do not receive bonuses or TR
no current global event in generation 1

Special Cases
---
max global parameters may not be affected again for rest of game
Volcanic Eruptions trigger ocean bonus at 0C -> first player places ocean but receives no bonuses
Snow Cover lowers temp below 0C -> nothing happens, but ocean bonus maynow be triggered again

Final Scoring
---
Turmoil step is not performed when the game ends
last step in scoring: all party leaders and the chairman are worth 1vp for that player







